This article is a presidential memorandum from August 30, 2011, regarding the waiver of a restriction on providing funds to the Palestinian Authority. The memorandum states that it is important to the national security interests of the United States to waive the provisions of a specific section of the Department of State, Foreign Operations, and Related Programs Appropriations Act, in order to provide funds to the Palestinian Authority. The Secretary of State is directed to transmit this determination to Congress, along with a report, and to publish it in the Federal Register. The memorandum is signed by President Barack Obama.